New Records: Travis Head scored an unbeaten 154, his highest ODI score
Australia successfully chased down a 316-run target with six overs to spare
Australia recorded their 13th consecutive ODI win
Key Match Events: England collapsed to 315 all out after a strong start
Travis Head took advantage of being dropped on six to make a century
Marnus Labuschagne contributed 77 in an unbroken 148-run stand with Head
Spin bowlers played a crucial role in England's collapse
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook commented on England's performance and the toss decision
Ricky Ponting praised Travis Head's performance and the team's environment
Stuart Broad called Travis Head an 'incredible player' and highlighted his powerplay strength
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia fielded a depleted line-up due to illness and injury
Will Jacks and Adam Zampa made significant contributions
